			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Adapt or Exit with style.<a name="62269"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Sep 15 04 11:15 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I see a few 
<br />
<i>&quot;Good bye I am hangin up my drum because of the Yes I’m leaving do to the recent PBAE nurf&quot;</i> 
<br />
type messages. 
<br />

<br />
On one hand I shake my head, thinking &quot;I think that person was just looking for an excuse, they must be really burned out. They should take a step away.&quot;
<br />

<br />
On another hand I shake my head thinking &quot;Yep bandwagon jumper.. cry FOUL and make threats and maybe they will fix the game feature. Understandable, they are frustrated too&quot;
<br />

<br />
On another hand I think to myself.
<br />

<br />
-Yes I have played EQ on and off since beta, with a long 2 years straight around the time Velious went live and a solid year when PoP went live
<br />

<br />
-Yes lots of aspects of this class have changed.
<br />

<br />
-I have never once seen a Bard AOE kite in my life. I loved chanting and grouping. I hate raiding its boring.
<br />

<br />
I also think back to the stealth nerf in DAoC and think. &quot;No way does a change to the AoE functionality equate the complete devastation of my stealth minstrel in DAoC when in March of 2002 they killed my favorite character's primary skill spec with no recourse&quot;
<br />

<br />
I am not saying anything negative towards those folks who post those &quot;That's it I quit!!&quot; messages.
<br />

<br />
The AoE thing is more than likely, a great opportunity to exit a tired, old, uninventive leveling grind game that's changed and shaped itself over the years into a odd tactical &quot;stuph whore mutual dependency-zerg for teh win addiction&quot;
<br />

<br />
A lot of players have put years and months of REAL time in their human lives into EQ. Consider it an experience. It's not  really that great of a game. But it is a matured game, and even a crappy bottle of cheesy California Merlot can taste smoothe after 5 years. Especially when shared with friends.
<br />

<br />
I am posting this quasi rambling post, mostly inspired for a few reasons. It is not intended to hurt anyone's feelings, but some of the things I say may strike a chord with some of you. (no pun intended)
<br />

<br />
-EQ is and was the first real time 3d MMP game. Prior to beta Ultima Online was pretty much the only game of its scale or magnitude. EQ is and was then *very* different character advancement model from UO. In fact no developer has even tried to emulate either since. They are both unique animals with tremendous innovations, and tremendous lack of progressive innovation in the same light.
<br />

<br />
-EQ won the sales war over the years for a number of good reasons. It hooked hardcore players, but being hardcore did not necessarily mean anything more than dedication. To reap rewards of outstanding proportions such as well this..
<br />

<br />
<a target="_new" href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=365770">http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=365770</a>
<br />

<br />
Nice stuff yes? Sure it is! This person played a long long time. They probably have thousands of memories, hundreds of raids, many many many stories about their years as a great EQ Bard.
<br />

<br />
Everyone knows character power equals rewards of outstanding proportions (stuph!) and of course EXP (AAs) or time.
<br />

<br />
You can't buy the truly great &quot;stuph&quot; in the bazaar, it is a trophy of exquisite power from raids. When you and your guildmates band together and using your superb knowledge of team work, understanding of what your class is supposed to do in a militaritsic execution format, and well, everyone's &quot;stuph&quot; and lots of hard work and time to get more &quot;stuph&quot;
<br />

<br />
Stuph increases your character power. It is a nice trophy of sorts to show your friends, spend time setting up a neat-0 Magelo profile so people can see something more interesting and unique than
<br />

<br />
&quot;You have played 228 days 17 hours 6 minutes and 11 seconds&quot;
<br />

<br />
or
<br />

<br />
&quot;you have killed 49,550,299 MOBs&quot;
<br />

<br />
or
<br />

<br />
&quot;You have participated in 688 raids where you pulsed 7,255,410 tics of various songs&quot;
<br />

<br />
Every game has &quot;rewards&quot; I am not making fun of the accomnplishements of many of the players out there, especially the ones who are a little tired of things &quot;constantly being messed up&quot; for years on end.
<br />

<br />
But go try Lineage 2. And you will appreciate the finer art of group combat that exists in EQ because Lineage is about as well designed as a wet paper bag in the lingere department. You will shake your head in disbelief at how such a game with so few features even has subscribers. 
<br />

<br />
For me I have been a unique animal. I have played all the MMP games with UO, DAoC, and EQ being the 3 that earned permanent residency on 4 computers over 5 years. My personal experiences were that I loved my infiltrator and my envenom minstrel in DAoC more, but lord my Bard in EQ sure is versatile. But there isn't much I can do, and I just don't want to 2 box again like I used to. I'm happy grouping from time to time where I can earn AAs. but now a race to 70 begins, so maybe I will grind some exp in pick up groups. it won't affect my guild, they all left the game when Elements of Darkness expired on CT and I just could not stand the DKP whores on Stormhammer (even adults can be selfish little kids for $40 a month)
<br />

<br />
I am rambling quite profusely so let me try and make a few points.
<br />

<br />
-If you have been a hardcore EQ player for eons and you want to &quot;hang up your drum&quot; sure get it off your chest. Go try some other MMP games. some have nice features and they all have much better graphics. They are not as complete as EQ quite simply because of the 5 years that EQ was able to mature and got constant development beyond a &quot;token live team&quot; like most MMP games end up with.
<br />

<br />
-Tell everyone.
<br />

<br />
<i>&quot;Hey folks. Gosh I don't know what to say, but inside I feel frustrated and EQ is not living up to that magical dream it once had for me. I am going to leave the game. I may be back, but I am not sure. If I don't come back I wish you all the best&quot;</i>
<br />

<br />
I think that is a nice exit with style personally.
<br />

<br />
Some of the other postings, well.... they have a tad too much Captain Kirk in them. Don't be offended, it just &quot;comes off&quot; that way with how things are phrased.
<br />

<br />
&quot;KHHHHhhhhhhhaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaan&quot;
<br />

<br />
Ok ok I am being mean sorry<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" /> I am just teasing. take break from EQ, while you were here you missed the see hidden stealth nerf in DAoC, the 1 on 1 assassin wars to zerg festivals, the implementation of spell crafting utterly and completely nerfing melee damage.
<br />

<br />
You missed seeing UO turn from a PvP murder count game of tension into a happy land with two shards!
<br />

<br />
You missed seeing kiting removed from Anarchy Online where all mobs teleport contantly on you for free hits if you try and run.
<br />

<br />
You missed the Hero system in AC2
<br />

<br />
You missed seeing triple strike daggers become god in AC1 and then each combat skill getting so much love they all ended up too powerful.
<br />

<br />
You missed using splitpea to figure out your second taper for Imperil VI in AC1 and the removal of comps in the game.
<br />

<br />
You missed a Diablo 2 expansion! It was pretty fun!
<br />
 
<br />
You missed the launch of NWN using the 3rd edition ruleset, and that in itself is nothing, but there are hundreds of USER persistent worlds, h*ll I designed 3 for fun on my own time when I was not designing real games making other people wealthy! 
<br />
<i>http://sibe.zftp.com/gallery1.html</i>
<br />

<br />
Probably some of the coolest rock paper sscissors PvP you will ever see.
<br />

<br />
You missed world of disney.. er.. I mean warcraft ...well you have to admit it looks like Disney!
<br />

<br />
You missed SIMS online going from a quirky single player game into the #2 cyber sex game<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-4.gif" border="0" alt="Tongue out" hspace="2" />NWn is still number 1
<br />

<br />
You missed some whacky space online games and some silly anime online game which I will not waste strokes on my keyboards typing in their names.
<br />

<br />
You missed a lot of stuff. Atlan weapons, Lifebane boost, itemization of Albion, player apartments in a futuristic rubi-ka, devastating criticals, and weaponmasters!
<br />

<br />
So hang up your drum, or blue noter or other &quot;thingie that works like a musical instrument but refuses to actually look like one&quot; and take a step back.
<br />

<br />
Go farm adena, see how worthless a wolf pet quest can be, meet interesting people from Korea with character names like ggggggggggggk, or &quot;redlove&quot; or aZnK1ll()ChInese
<br />

<br />
There are kids in MMP games now that were what 10 years old when some of you got your Epic. So go expand, try some other games, focus on your real life even better! I feel sure there is someone out there who would love to have their old friend back, or wife or husband who has buried their nose at &quot;some camp&quot; for far too long!
<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />
</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
