				<td colspan="2"><span>I thought I'd add my feelings to this thread. EQ is a game, hobby, entrtainment venue, whatever you prefer to call it. As such, SOE is primarily a service company. When said service company decides to announce the pushback of an expansion release for the express purpose of adressing community concerns (read: to improve customer service) and then fails to deliver on its promise to do so, people get upset. 
<br />

<br />
Me, I finally took a hard look at exactly what I was recieving from sony in the way of customer service. Would I accept any service company I deal with ignoring communications of dissatisfaction? Would I accept any service company lying baltantly and unabashedly about any manner of things (no new nerfs, delay of ooW to deal with issues, things on top 10 issues lists under consideration)? The answer is obviously no. I would take my business elsewhere.
<br />

<br />
Now, I'm not considering cancelling my accounts due to the PBAE nerf, I thought it was well-considered and probably overdue. Also, I'm not considering cancelling because I find the current state of the game uninteresting and unchallenging. Or because I feel that all 10 of our issues should have already been acted upon and implemented, frankly some I think will hurt our class more than help. All that said, I find the lack of meaningful communication to resolve dissatisfaction within the playerbase to be both demeaning and arrogant. THAT is why, if I hang up my drum (not decided yet), I will do so. Their business model obviously accepts the loss of longtime customers due to lack of resolution of difficulty. It must. If it didn't my concerns would not exist. There would BE customer service.
<br />

<br />
A bard of a different color
<br />
Kula</span></td>
